cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software / pipeline, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Structural Isomorphism: cross-domain SOC validation pipeline"
authors:
  - family-names: dada8899
    affiliation: "Independent Research, Structural Isomorphism Project"
version: 0.3.1
date-released: 2026-05-14
url: "https://github.com/dada8899/structural-isomorphism"
repository-code: "https://github.com/dada8899/structural-isomorphism"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  A Clauset-grade analysis pipeline for cross-domain validation of self-
  organized criticality (SOC), preferential attachment, and adjacent
  universality classes (Motter-Lai network cascade, Preisach hysteresis,
  Scheffer fold bifurcation). One shared ~339-LOC Python module
  (v4/lib/soc_pipeline.py) applied unchanged to thirteen independent
  empirical systems plus four synthetic null controls. Includes a B1/B3
  multi-model LLM ensemble critic over a 21-candidate universality-class
  taxonomy, frozen pipeline source, and 213 tests across unit /
  integration / e2e tiers. Companion preprint
  (paper/v0-unified-pipeline-2026-05-13.md) and dataset bundle
  (dataset/v1/) ship in the same repository.
keywords:
  - self-organized criticality
  - cross-domain validation
  - power-law
  - Clauset MLE
  - universality classes
  - Omori-Utsu
  - preferential attachment
  - Motter-Lai cascade
  - Preisach hysteresis
  - Scheffer fold bifurcation
  - LLM ensemble critic
  - reproducibility benchmark
